- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper uses time series models to predict the overlap between high centrality nodes in current and future time steps. 
- cs.SOC (Computational Social Science) is a possible category as the paper deals with social networks and their structure. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also a possible category as the paper proposes algorithms for identifying influential nodes in time-varying networks.
